== Production ==

=== Development ===
After ''[[Andhrawala]]'' (2004), [[Puri Jagannadh]] and [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.]] tried to collaborate for another movie several times which could not happen. When reports of their second collaboration emerged in early 2014, neither of them confirmed about the film. During the post release promotions of ''[[Heart Attack (film)|Heart Attack]]'' (2014), Jagannadh stated that he planning to make a film based solely on family values in his next venture with Godavari shores and regional backdrop.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/120-openings-for-heart-attack-everywhere-puri-jagannadh-interview--telugu-news-102958|title=120% Openings For 'Heart Attack' Everywhere: Puri Jagannadh [Interview]|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=1 February 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129020613/http://www.indiaglitz.com/120-openings-for-heart-attack-everywhere-puri-jagannadh-interview--telugu-news-102958|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> [[B. V. S. N. Prasad]] was expected to produce this film under [[Sri Venkateswara Cine Chitra]] banner.<ref name="April">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-from-April/articleshow/32239417.cms|title=NTR, Puri Jagannadh film from April?|author=[[Times News Network|TNN]]|publisher=''[[The Times of India]]''|date=18 March 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129020955/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-from-April/articleshow/32239417.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> He left to [[Bangkok]] in the end of March 2014 for writing the story of this project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-writing-script-for-NTR-Jr/articleshow/32541941.cms|title=Puri writing script for NTR Jr?|last=Pasupulate|first=Karthik|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=22 March 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129021132/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-writing-script-for-NTR-Jr/articleshow/32541941.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref>

[[Bandla Ganesh]] was confirmed to produce the film under [[Parameswara Art Productions]] banner. When Jagannadh was about to begin work on the film, Rama Rao Jr. asked him to listen to a point narrated by [[Vakkantham Vamsi|Vamsi]] to him four years back and the former agreed saying that he would definitely do the film if it is good than his story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Launch-Details-telugu-news-124163|title='Temper' audio launch details|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129042632/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Launch-Details-telugu-news-124163|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> Jagannadh chose to direct the script written by Vamsi in mid May 2014 which marked the former's first film whose story was not written by him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-Jagan-to-direct-Vakkantams-story/articleshow/35100086.cms|title=Puri Jagan to direct Vakkantam's story|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=14 May 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129021239/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-Jagan-to-direct-Vakkantams-story/articleshow/35100086.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The script work was in progress by late May 2014 and film was declared a [[Police procedural|cop drama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-to-play-a-cop-in-Puris-film/articleshow/35832671.cms|title=NTR to play a cop in Puri's film|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=31 May 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129021421/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-to-play-a-cop-in-Puris-film/articleshow/35832671.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref>

In late June 2014, [[Devi Sri Prasad]] was selected as the music director of the film while the cast and crew were being finalized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/DSP-to-score-music-for-NTRs-next-film/articleshow/36824384.cms|title=DSP to score music for NTR's next film|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=20 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129021515/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/DSP-to-score-music-for-NTRs-next-film/articleshow/36824384.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The film was confirmed to be launched officially on 1 August 2014 at Jagannadh's new office ''Cave'' at 7:00 AM.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Muhurat-fixed-for-ntr-puri-jagannadh-movie-opening-telugu-news-111106|title=Muhurat fixed for NTR-Puri Jagannadh movie opening|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=30 July 2014|accessdate=30 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129021934/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Muhurat-fixed-for-ntr-puri-jagannadh-movie-opening-telugu-news-111106|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> [[Shyam K. Naidu]] was declared as the cinematographer, S. R. Sekhar was declared as the editor, Brahma Kadali was declared as the art director while [[FEFSI Vijayan]] was recruited to compose the fights.<ref name="launch">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/functions1/muhurat-ntr-purijagannadhfilm.html|title=NTR-Puri Jagannadh new movie launch|publisher=[[Idlebrain.com]]|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=1 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022105/http://www.idlebrain.com/news/functions1/muhurat-ntr-purijagannadhfilm.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref>

Devi Sri Prasad was replaced by [[Anoop Rubens]] later for unknown reasons while [[Mani Sharma]] was selected for composing the background score while Anoop Rubens composed the soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/dsp-out-anoop-rubens-in-for-ntrs-film-telugu-news-115254|title=DSP out, Anoop Rubens in for NTR's film|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=29 September 2014|accessdate=5 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022226/http://www.indiaglitz.com/dsp-out-anoop-rubens-in-for-ntrs-film-telugu-news-115254|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/115328.html|title=Mani Sharma for BGM of NTR-Puri film ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=30 September 2014|accessdate=5 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022319/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/115328.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The titles ''Kummutha'', ''Kummestha'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntr-puri-bandla-ganesh-film-titled-kummutha--telugu-news-106451|title=NTR - Puri - Bandla Ganesh film titled 'Kummutha' ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=21 April 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022426/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntr-puri-bandla-ganesh-film-titled-kummutha--telugu-news-106451|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> ''Rubabu'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-titled-Rubabu-telugu-news-108636|title=NTR - Puri Jagannadh film titled 'Rubabu'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022536/http://www.indiaglitz.com/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-titled-Rubabu-telugu-news-108636|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> ''Temper'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News-Interviews/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-titled-Temper/articleshow/38016074.cms|title=NTR, Puri Jagannadh film titled Temper?|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=8 July 2014|accessdate=9 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022637/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News-Interviews/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-titled-Temper/articleshow/38016074.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> ''Nenorakam'' with the tagline "Totally Corrupted"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News/NTRs-new-film-is-titled-Nenorakam/articleshow/39241837.cms|title=NTR's new film is titled Nenorakam|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=29 July 2014|accessdate=30 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022734/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News/NTRs-new-film-is-titled-Nenorakam/articleshow/39241837.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> and ''Shamsher''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/117906.html|title=NTR -Puri film titled 'Shamsher' ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=5 November 2014|accessdate=5 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129022852/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/117906.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> were considered by the makers and ''Temper'' was finalized and announced on 19 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Confirmed-:-Ntr---Puri-Jagannadh-Film-Titled-temper-telugu-news-119004|title=Confirmed : NTR - Puri Jagannadh film titled 'Temper'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=19 November 2014|accessdate=19 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129023012/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Confirmed-:-Ntr---Puri-Jagannadh-Film-Titled-temper-telugu-news-119004|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The film was rumored to be facing financial troubles in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141226/nation-current-affairs/article/tollywood-nearly-broke|title=Tollywood is nearly broke|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''[[Deccan Chronicle]]''|date=26 December 2014|accessdate=26 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141226051356/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141226/nation-current-affairs/article/tollywood-nearly-broke|archivedate=26 December 2014}}</ref>

