Kajal Aggarwal was selected as the heroine of this film in early June 2013 pairing with Rama Rao Jr. after two successful films ''[[Brindavanam (film)|Brindavanam]]'' (2010) and ''[[Baadshah (2013 film)|Baadshah]]'' (2013) whose inclusion was confirmed by Jagannadh in a statement to the media after few days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/will-kajal-junior-ntr-make-hattrick-of-hits/article6086689.ece|title=Will Kajal, Junior NTR make hat-trick of hits|author=[[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]]|publisher=''[[The Hindu]]''|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128165556/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/will-kajal-junior-ntr-make-hattrick-of-hits/article6086689.ece|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kajal-Aggarwal-to-romance-NTR/articleshow/35997836.cms|title=Kajal Aggarwal to romance NTR|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=3 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128165710/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kajal-Aggarwal-to-romance-NTR/articleshow/35997836.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> [[Ajaz Khan]] was signed as the antagonist of the film in July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news/Big-Boss-Fame-Ajaz-now-the-Telugu-villian/articleshow/37905665.cms|title=Big Boss Fame Ajaz now the Telugu villian|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=6 July 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128165827/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news/Big-Boss-Fame-Ajaz-now-the-Telugu-villian/articleshow/37905665.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> On the day of launch, it was confirmed that [[Prakash Raj]], [[Madhuurima]], [[Ali (actor)|Ali]], [[Kota Srinivasa Rao]] and [[Posani Krishna Murali]] would play important roles along with [[Tanikella Bharani]], [[Penmatsa Subbaraju|Subbaraju]], [[Vennela Kishore]], [[Jaya Prakash Reddy]], Sapthagiri, [[Ramaprabha]], Pavithra Lokesh and [[Kovai Sarala]].<ref name="launch"/> Kajal had shortage of bulk dates to accommodate and it was rumored that [[Tamannaah]] or a new actress would replace her.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Kajal-opts-out-of-NTRs-film/articleshow/39684200.cms|title=Kajal opts out of NTR's film?|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=5 August 2014|accessdate=8 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170010/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Kajal-opts-out-of-NTRs-film/articleshow/39684200.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140805/entertainment-tollywood/article/date-jinx-ntr-jr-puri-jagannath-film|title=Date jinx in NTR Jr, Puri Jagannath film|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=5 August 2014|accessdate=8 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170115/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140805/entertainment-tollywood/article/date-jinx-ntr-jr-puri-jagannath-film|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref>

Ganesh denied those rumors and confirmed Kajal's inclusion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140807/entertainment-tollywood/article/kajal-aggarwal%E2%80%99s-role-confirmed|title=Kajal Aggarwal<U+2019>s role confirmed|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=7 August 2014|accessdate=8 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170211/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140807/entertainment-tollywood/article/kajal-aggarwal%E2%80%99s-role-confirmed|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Though initially planned to shoot simultaneously for a film by [[Sudhir Mishra]], Kajal opted to continue with this film due to certain problems with Mishra's script.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Spoilt-for-choice/articleshow/46023296.cms|title=Spoilt for choice|last=Pudipeddi|first=Haricharan|publisher=''[[Bangalore Mirror]]''|date=26 January 2015|accessdate=27 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150127065529/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Spoilt-for-choice/articleshow/46023296.cms?|archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref> [[S. Sreesanth]] and [[Zarine Khan]] were speculated to be a part of the film's cast when they visited Jagannath's ''Cave'' but there was no official confirmation then.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140811/entertainment-tollywood/article/special-visitors-drop-%E2%80%98cave%E2%80%99|title=Sreesanth and Zarine Khan drop by at Puri Jagannadh's <U+2018>Cave<U+2019>|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=11 August 2014|accessdate=12 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170330/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140811/entertainment-tollywood/article/special-visitors-drop-%E2%80%98cave%E2%80%99|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Sreesanth-to-act-in-ntr-puri-jagannadh-film--telugu-news-111869|title=Sreesanth to act in NTR - Puri Jagannadh film ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=12 August 2014|accessdate=12 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170416/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Sreesanth-to-act-in-ntr-puri-jagannadh-film--telugu-news-111869|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> [[Mrudhula Bhaskar|Naveena]] was reported to be considered for a small role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140819/entertainment-tollywood/article/puri-jagannath-eyes-ram-gopal-varma%E2%80%99s-actress|title=Puri Jagannath eyes Ram Gopal Varma<U+2019>s actress!|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=19 August 2014|accessdate=21 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170523/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140819/entertainment-tollywood/article/puri-jagannath-eyes-ram-gopal-varma%E2%80%99s-actress|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Impressed with his previous works, Jagannadh casted [[Saptagiri (actor)|Sapthagiri]] for a special comedy role in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/saptagiris-special-role-in-puris-film.html|title=Saptagiri<U+2019>s special role in Puri<U+2019>s film|publisher=[[123telugu.com]]|date=9 September 2014|accessdate=12 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170658/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/saptagiris-special-role-in-puris-film.html|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> [[Nora Fatehi]] replaced [[Shruti Haasan]] in an [[item number]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shruti-Sizzles-In-Telugu-Item-Songs:-tamil-news-115677|title=Shruti sizzles in Telugu Item songs|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=5 October 2014|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170948/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shruti-Sizzles-In-Telugu-Item-Songs:-tamil-news-115677|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Norah-Fatehi-Shakes-A-Leg-With-Ntr-telugu-news-115764|title=Norah Fatehi shakes a leg with NTR|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=6 October 2014|accessdate=28 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128170856/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Norah-Fatehi-Shakes-A-Leg-With-Ntr-telugu-news-115764|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Jagannadh immediately selected her after her intense training to prepare for her role as a commando in the film ''[[Roar: Tigers of the Sundarbans]]'' (2014).<ref name="Nora">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-dances-like-a-dream-Nora-Fatehi/articleshow/45435183.cms|title=NTR dances like a dream: Nora Fatehi|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=9 December 2014|accessdate=10 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141210023045/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-dances-like-a-dream-Nora-Fatehi/articleshow/45435183.cms|archivedate=10 December 2014}}</ref>

[[R. Narayana Murthy]] was approached for a special character in the film opposite Rama Rao Jr. Murthy liked the role but declined it as he did not want to move to mainstream cinema and was content making [[Parallel Cinema|left-oriented films]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/When-Narayana-Murthy-turned-down-NTR-Jr/articleshow/45943152.cms|title=When Narayana Murthy turned down NTR Jr|last=Prakash|first=B. V. S.|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=19 January 2015|accessdate=20 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150120033119/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/When-Narayana-Murthy-turned-down-NTR-Jr/articleshow/45943152.cms?|archivedate=20 January 2015}}</ref> [[Sonia Agarwal]] was signed on to play a significant role in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-01-27/NTR-confident-of-pulling-off-Temper-alone-128117|title=NTR confident of pulling off Temper alone|publisher=''[[The Hans India]]''|date=27 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128031809/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-01-27/NTR-confident-of-pulling-off-Temper-alone-128117|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref> Apoorva Srinivasan was cast for a small yet crucial supporting role marking her debut in Telugu cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Apoorva-Srinivasan-talks-about-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46244259.cms|title=Apoorva Srinivasan talks about NTR's Temper|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=15 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150215050221/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Apoorva-Srinivasan-talks-about-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46244259.cms?|archivedate=15 February 2015}}</ref>

=== Characters and looks ===
N. T. Rama Rao Jr. was reported to be seen as a tough and eccentric police officer in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Is-NTR-playing-a-cop-again/articleshow/36334617.cms|title=Is NTR playing a cop again?|last=Pasupulate|first=Karthik|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=9 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143156/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Is-NTR-playing-a-cop-again/articleshow/36334617.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-Jr-to-play-cop-in-Puris-next/articleshow/36491835.cms|title=NTR Jr to play cop in Puri<U+2019>s next?|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=13 June 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143301/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/NTR-Jr-to-play-cop-in-Puris-next/articleshow/36491835.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Regarding her character in the film, Madhuurima said that she plays a crucial role which is the turning point in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Madhuurima-bags-her-first-film-with-NTR-Jr/articleshow/39486658.cms|title=Madhuurima bags her first film with NTR Jr|last=A.S.|first=Sasidhar|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=3 August 2014|accessdate=3 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143556/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Madhuurima-bags-her-first-film-with-NTR-Jr/articleshow/39486658.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> She later added that her role is a small one that changes the course of the protagonist's character graph.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Madhuurima-pitted-opposite-Sunny-Leone/articleshow/46056060.cms|title=Madhuurima pitted opposite Sunny Leone|last=Sashidhar|first=A. S.|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150130043256/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Madhuurima-pitted-opposite-Sunny-Leone/articleshow/46056060.cms?|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref> Kajal Aggarwal was confirmed to play the role of an animal lover in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/junior-ntr-puri-jagannadh-new-film-slated-for-makar-sankranti/article1-1247547.aspx|title=Junior NTR-Puri Jagannadh new film slated for Makar Sankranti|author=IANS|publisher=''[[Hindustan Times]]''|date=2 August 2014|accessdate=22 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143451/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/junior-ntr-puri-jagannadh-new-film-slated-for-makar-sankranti/article1-1247547.aspx|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> For his role, Rama Rao Jr. hired a new trainer who specialises in improving muscle tone and shed few kilograms relying on high protein diet and workout routine to build a hefty body. He also sported a crew cut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/did-you-know-/NTR-Jr-muscling-up/articleshow/44835947.cms|title=NTR Jr muscling up|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=17 October 2014|accessdate=20 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143730/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/did-you-know-/NTR-Jr-muscling-up/articleshow/44835947.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> A few still images of the film were leaked online on 26 November 2014 which confirmed Rama Rao Jr.'s look in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-Leaked-Pics-telugu-news-119581|title=NTR's 'Temper' leaked pics|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143849/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-Leaked-Pics-telugu-news-119581|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref>

Those stills were captured during the shoot at Goa and they went viral on social networking sites.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-goes-shirtless-temper-leaked-photos-go-viral-photos-615233|title=Junior NTR Goes Shirtless for 'Temper'; Leaked Pictures Go Viral [Photos]|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128143941/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-goes-shirtless-temper-leaked-photos-go-viral-photos-615233|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> However the makers tried to find out who leaked it online as they wanted the pictures to be released to create a buzz before the film's launch.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Leaked-shirtless-pics-of-NTR-from-Temper/articleshow/45285845.cms|title=Leaked shirtless pics of NTR from Temper|last=A.S.|first=Sasidhar|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128144047/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Leaked-shirtless-pics-of-NTR-from-Temper/articleshow/45285845.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Another still was leaked on the next day which featured Rama Rao Jr. sitting on a [[Royal Enfield (India)|Royal Enfield]] bike sans shirt sporting his six pack abs. The image was a working still taken on the beach reportedly featuring in a song sequence of the film. However, none from the film's unit made a statement about the alleged leak.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-look-junior-ntrs-2nd-shirtless-photo-leaked-why-puri-jagannath-silent-615355|title='Temper' First Look: Junior NTR's 2nd Shirtless Photo Leaked; Why is Puri Jagannath Silent?|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=28 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128144154/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-look-junior-ntrs-2nd-shirtless-photo-leaked-why-puri-jagannath-silent-615355|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref>

Rama Rao Jr.'s underwent a drastic physical transformation from head to toe in hairdo, costumes, body and attitude for this role. His stylist Ashwin Mawle shopped for the costumes and accessories from designer stores in [[Hong Kong]] and [[London]]. Regarding the styling, Ashwin further revealed, "For the hair, we tried getting a few variations of spikes <U+2014> straight, cross and messy. He (Rama Rao Jr.) keeps a tab on the latest trends. He took a lot of references from latest runway looks and zeroed in on an earthy color palette: brown, burgundy and grey. Thick jackets make him look bulkier, so he has gone for slim fit shirts and jackets made of linen" in an interview to Sasidhar AS of ''[[The Times of India]]''. He added that N. T. Rama Rao Jr. trimmed his mustache for sporting a rugged look.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-new-look-in-Temper-decoded/articleshow/45396889.cms|title=NTR<U+2019>s new look in Temper decoded|last=A.S.|first=Sasidhar|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=7 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141207055653/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-new-look-in-Temper-decoded/articleshow/45396889.cms?|archivedate=7 December 2014}}</ref>

Madhuurima said in an interview to Suresh Kavirayani of ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'' that she participated in few action sequences with Rama Rao Jr. in the film and added that she has no songs with him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141208/entertainment-tollywood/article/big-pongal-madhuurima|title=Big Pongal for Madhuurima|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=8 December 2014|accessdate=9 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141209050047/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141208/entertainment-tollywood/article/big-pongal-madhuurima|archivedate=9 December 2014}}</ref> Rama Rao Jr.'s character was named Daya and he was shown as a sub inspector of police who by his own admission is ruthless, fully corrupted, criminal minded and 100% cunning.<ref name="Trailer OIE">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/temper-trailer-review-jr-ntr-in-and-as-172016.html|title='Temper' Trailer Review: Jr.NTR In & As!|author=Veena|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129043511/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/temper-trailer-review-jr-ntr-in-and-as-172016.html|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> For a particular scene where he had to walk with bare chest, Rama Rao Jr. skipped drinking a glass of water for 18 hours continuously.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/NTR-goes-without-water-for-18-hrs/articleshow/46058163.cms|title=NTR goes without water for 18 hrs!|last=Vivan|first=Sridhar|publisher=''Bangalore Mirror''|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150130043628/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/NTR-goes-without-water-for-18-hrs/articleshow/46058163.cms?|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref> Kajal said in an interview to IANS that her character would become the reason for the transformation in the protagonist's character after she forces him to take up an issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/kajal-aggarwal-fatherhood-has-brought-intensity-to-jr-ntrs-performance/|title=Kajal Aggarwal: Fatherhood has brought intensity to Jr NTR<U+2019>s performance!|author=IANS|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=10 February 2015|accessdate=10 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150210100948/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/kajal-aggarwal-fatherhood-has-brought-intensity-to-jr-ntrs-performance/|archivedate=10 February 2015}}</ref> Posani Krishna Murali was seen in the role of a sincere constable who hates Daya because of his corrupt nature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/He-Can-Play-Serious-Roles-Too-telugu-news-125550|title=He can play serious roles too|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150214112100/http://www.indiaglitz.com/He-Can-Play-Serious-Roles-Too-telugu-news-125550|archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref>

=== Filming ===
[[File:Goa (44).jpg|thumb|Goa, where the initial scenes were shot]]
The regular shooting was planned to commence in April 2014.<ref name="April"/> In mid-May 2014, the film's shooting schedules were planned in July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-Jagannadh-to-direct-Jr-NTR/articleshow/35343070.cms|title=Puri Jagannadh to direct Jr NTR|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=19 May 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171318/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Puri-Jagannadh-to-direct-Jr-NTR/articleshow/35343070.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> On 1 July 2014 it was declared that the film's shoot would be completed in 100 working days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/ntr-puri-film-to-be-finished-in-100-days-news-telugu-ohbmUKeedabhh.html|title=NTR - Puri film to be finished in 100 days|publisher=[[Sify]]|date=1 July 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171430/http://www.sify.com/movies/ntr-puri-film-to-be-finished-in-100-days-news-telugu-ohbmUKeedabhh.html|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Principal photography began on 2 August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-launched/articleshow/39411001.cms|title=NTR-Puri Jagannadh film launched|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=1 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171540/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News/NTR-Puri-Jagannadh-film-launched/articleshow/39411001.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Madhuurima joined the film's sets on 9 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140803/entertainment-tollywood/article/madhuurima-gets-big-one|title=Madhuurima gets a big one|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=3 August 2014|accessdate=3 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171632/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140803/entertainment-tollywood/article/madhuurima-gets-big-one|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> N. T. Rama Rao Jr. was expected to join the film's sets on 11 August though he joined on 21 August in the Aluminium Factory at [[Gachibowli]] in Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-to-join-the-sets-of-puri-jagannadhs-film-on-11th-telugu-news-111706|title=NTR to join the sets of Puri Jagannadh's film on 11th|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=9 August 2014|accessdate=9 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171807/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-to-join-the-sets-of-puri-jagannadhs-film-on-11th-telugu-news-111706|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-to-join-the-sets-of-Puri-Jagannadhs-Nenorakam/articleshow/40516664.cms|title=NTR to join the sets of Puri Jagannadh's Nenorakam|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=20 August 2014|accessdate=21 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128171914/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-to-join-the-sets-of-Puri-Jagannadhs-Nenorakam/articleshow/40516664.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Jr-begins-shooting-for-Puri-Jagans-film/articleshow/40616942.cms|title=NTR Jr begins shooting for Puri Jagan's film|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=21 August 2014|accessdate=22 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172111/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Jr-begins-shooting-for-Puri-Jagans-film/articleshow/40616942.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Few comedy scenes were shot on Rama Rao Jr., Vennela Kishore and other supporting cast after a week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Jr-shooting-for-comic-scenes/articleshow/41090114.cms|title=NTR Jr. shooting for comic scenes|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=28 August 2014|accessdate=1 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172226/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Jr-shooting-for-comic-scenes/articleshow/41090114.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> The film's second schedule was planned from 10 September till the completion of the film's shoot which was postponed to 15 September because of disruption in construction of a large police station set due to rainfall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-puri-Jagannadh-Film-Second-Schedule-From-10th-telugu-news-113369|title=NTR-Puri Jagannadh film second schedule from 10th|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=4 September 2014|accessdate=4 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172322/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-puri-Jagannadh-Film-Second-Schedule-From-10th-telugu-news-113369|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140911/entertainment-tollywood/article/delayed-start-ntr-jr%E2%80%99s-film|title=Delayed start for NTR Jr<U+2019>s film|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=11 September 2014|accessdate=12 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172422/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140911/entertainment-tollywood/article/delayed-start-ntr-jr%E2%80%99s-film|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref>

After being rumored that the film might be shelved after shooting was stopped midway, Bandla Ganesh has clarified that the shooting would continue from 26 September and the shooting resumed in Aluminium Factory at Gachibowli in Hyderabad and the makers announced that the schedule would continue till the end of the principal photography.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr---Puri-Jagannadh-Movie-Second-Schedule-From-26th-telugu-news-114800|title=NTR - Puri Jagannadh movie second schedule from 26th|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=23 September 2014|accessdate=23 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172549/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr---Puri-Jagannadh-Movie-Second-Schedule-From-26th-telugu-news-114800|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/115092.html|title=NTR-Puri Jagannadh movie second schedule starts|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 September 2014|accessdate=26 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172636/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/115092.html|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> The makers selected a house in Begumpet to erect a special police station set to shoot few crucial scenes on which {{INR}}2.7 million was invested.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Special-police-station-set-for-NTRs-film/articleshow/44479684.cms|title=Special police station set for NTR<U+2019>s film|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=6 October 2014|accessdate=7 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172754/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Special-police-station-set-for-NTRs-film/articleshow/44479684.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> An item number on Rama Rao Jr. and Nora Fatehi was shot in Hyderabad in early October 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nora-Fatehi-grooves-with-NTR-in-Puri-Jagannadhs-film/articleshow/44417809.cms|title=Nora Fatehi grooves with NTR in Puri Jagannadh's film|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=5 October 2014|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128172900/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nora-Fatehi-grooves-with-NTR-in-Puri-Jagannadhs-film/articleshow/44417809.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> That song was a fast-paced folk song choreographed by Shekhar which Nora termed a "hyper energetic dance number".<ref name="Nora"/>

[[File:Ramoji Film City.jpg|thumb|left|[[Ramoji Film City]], where parts of the film were shot]]
25% of the film's shoot was wrapped up by then and the next schedule was planned in [[Vishakhapatnam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-completes-25-shoot.html|title=NTR, Puri film completes 25% shoot|publisher=123telugu.com|date=7 October 2014|accessdate=7 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128173012/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-completes-25-shoot.html|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Later the makers chose Goa to shoot major parts of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141010/entertainment-tollywood/article/ntr-jr-goa|title=NTR Jr in Goa|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=10 October 2014|accessdate=11 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129010644/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141010/entertainment-tollywood/article/ntr-jr-goa|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> Few scenes on Rama Rao Jr., Kajal Aggarwal and some other actors were shot meanwhile.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-And-Puri-Jagannadh-In-Goa-telugu-news-116227|title=NTR and Puri Jagannadh in Goa|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=12 October 2014|accessdate=13 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011136/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-And-Puri-Jagannadh-In-Goa-telugu-news-116227|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The film's Goa schedule was delayed due to the ongoing strike for Non-acceptance of the revised pay hike for the Film Federation Employees.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141019/entertainment-tollywood/article/strike-affects-puri-jagannath-ntr-jr-film|title=Strike affects Puri Jagannath, NTR Jr film|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=20 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011406/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141019/entertainment-tollywood/article/strike-affects-puri-jagannath-ntr-jr-film|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The strike was called off later and the filming continued from 25 October at Goa where major part of the film was shot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-to-resume-goa-schedule-from-oct-25.html|title=NTR-Puri film to resume Goa schedule from Oct 25|publisher=123telugu.com|date=23 October 2014|accessdate=23 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011540/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-to-resume-goa-schedule-from-oct-25.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Kajal-partying-in-Goa/articleshow/44949736.cms|title=NTR, Kajal partying in Goa|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=27 October 2014|accessdate=28 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011649/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Kajal-partying-in-Goa/articleshow/44949736.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The shoot of the interval block was wrapped up by 2 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-film-interval-block-complete.html|title=NTR film interval block complete|publisher=123telugu.com|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=2 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011817/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-film-interval-block-complete.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> Few key scenes on Rama Rao Jr., Kajal Aggarwal and Prakash Raj were shot later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-to-finish-goa-schedule-on-nov-23.html|title=NTR-Puri film to finish Goa schedule on Nov 23|publisher=123telugu.com|date=8 November 2014|accessdate=8 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129011935/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-puri-film-to-finish-goa-schedule-on-nov-23.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The Goa schedule came to an end on 24 November and the team returned to Hyderabad the next day.<ref name="editing">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-wraps-up-Goa-schedule/articleshow/45259316.cms|title=NTR's Temper wraps up Goa schedule|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=24 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129012041/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-wraps-up-Goa-schedule/articleshow/45259316.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The next schedule started at [[Ramoji Film City]] from 27 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntrs-rfc-schedule-to-start-tomorrow.html|title=NTR<U+2019>s RFC schedule to start tomorrow|publisher=123telugu.com|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129012144/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntrs-rfc-schedule-to-start-tomorrow.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> By then, 80% of the film's shoot was complete.<ref name="post prod">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Tempers-audio-to-be-launched-in-Guntur/articleshow/45285797.cms|title=Temper's audio to be launched in Guntur|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129012243/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Tempers-audio-to-be-launched-in-Guntur/articleshow/45285797.cms|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref>

The film's shoot was disrupted again due to another strike caused by Film Federation Employees to appoint those technicians who have a membership in the Federation. The makers said that two weeks of filming is pending which would start immediately once the strike is called off.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141202/entertainment-tollywood/article/holiday-halt-no-end-sight-tollywood-strike|title=Holiday Halt: No end in sight for Tollywood strike|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=3 December 2014|accessdate=3 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141203031549/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141202/entertainment-tollywood/article/holiday-halt-no-end-sight-tollywood-strike|archivedate=3 December 2014}}</ref> However, the film's shoot was reported to be progressing in Hyderabad with employees other than the ones from Federation being employed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141204/entertainment-tollywood/article/shoots-are-still|title=Shoots are still on|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=4 December 2014|accessdate=5 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141205051329/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141204/entertainment-tollywood/article/shoots-are-still|archivedate=5 December 2014}}</ref> The strike was called off on 5 December 2014 and the union members took part in the shootings from the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shootings-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120281|title=Shootings to resume from tomorrow|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=5 December 2014|accessdate=6 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141206030730/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shootings-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120281|archivedate=6 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/AP-Film-workers-calls-off-strike/articleshow/45396153.cms|title=AP Film workers calls off strike|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=7 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141207053843/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/AP-Film-workers-calls-off-strike/articleshow/45396153.cms?|archivedate=7 December 2014}}</ref> Bandla Ganesh called off the film's shoot for 10 days as Rama Rao Jr. was devastated because of the death of his step brother Nandamuri Janakiram.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/junior-ntr-bereaved-temper-shoot-halted/|title=Jr NTR in shock over brother Janakiram<U+2019>s death, producers halt <U+2018>Temper<U+2019> shoot|author=IANS|publisher=''[[Indian Express]]''|date=9 December 2014|accessdate=9 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141209094914/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/junior-ntr-bereaved-temper-shoot-halted/|archivedate=9 December 2014}}</ref> However Rama Rao Jr. chose to continue for ensuring a Sankranthi release and the filming resumed on 10 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Shooting-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120559|title='Temper' shooting to resume from tomorrow|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=9 December 2014|accessdate=9 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141209151741/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Shooting-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120559|archivedate=9 December 2014}}</ref>

{{Quote box|width=30%|align=right|quote="The film had a scene where N. T. Rama Rao Jr. playing the role of the cop gets into a confrontation with Prakash Raj and Kota Srinivasa Rao. When Puri Jagannadh narrated the scene, Rama Rao Jr. suggested it would be better to have it set in a courtroom."|source=&nbsp;<U+2014>A source from the film's unit in an interaction with ''The Times of India''.<ref name="court room">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Will-a-courtroom-scene-break-the-jinx-for-NTR/articleshow/46025707.cms|title=Will a courtroom scene break the jinx for NTR?|last=Sashidhar|first=A. S.|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=26 January 2015|accessdate=27 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150127060247/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Will-a-courtroom-scene-break-the-jinx-for-NTR/articleshow/46025707.cms?|archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref>}}
16 days of shoot was reported to be pending and the filming was expected to come to an end on 31 December 2014. Meanwhile Rama Rao Jr. participated in the shoot of some important jail and court scenes at a specially erected set in Aluminium Factory near Gachibowli.<ref name="Temper resumes">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-release-date-revealed-set-clash-pawan-kalyans-gopala-gopala-616708|title=Jr NTR's 'Temper' Release Date Revealed: Set to Clash with Pawan Kalyan's 'Gopala Gopala'|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=10 December 2014|accessdate=10 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141210101634/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-release-date-revealed-set-clash-pawan-kalyans-gopala-gopala-616708|archivedate=10 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-resumes-shoot/articleshow/45478320.cms|title=NTR's Temper resumes shoot|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=11 December 2014|accessdate=12 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141212014521/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-resumes-shoot/articleshow/45478320.cms?|archivedate=12 December 2014}}</ref> Puri Jagannadh informed Bandla Ganesh that the film cannot be completed as planned and that film will not be ready for a Sankranti release. The latter was fine with the decision and gave a break to Rama Rao Jr.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141214/entertainment-tollywood/article/sankrantis-high-hopes|title=Sankranti's high hopes|last=King|first=Vincent|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=14 December 2014|accessdate=15 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141215042339/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141214/entertainment-tollywood/article/sankrantis-high-hopes|archivedate=15 December 2014}}</ref> The filming resumed from 27 December 2014 in Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Trailer-Release-Date-telugu-news-121884|title='Temper' trailer release date|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=27 December 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141227100709/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Trailer-Release-Date-telugu-news-121884|archivedate=27 December 2014}}</ref> Scenes on Rama Rao Jr. and others were shot in a police station set and court room set erected in Begumpet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/temper-shoot-racing-ahead-in-begumpet.html|title=Temper shoot racing ahead in Begumpet|publisher=123telugu.com|date=30 December 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141230052317/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/temper-shoot-racing-ahead-in-begumpet.html|archivedate=30 December 2014}}</ref> The last song was shot on Rama Rao Jr. and Kajal Aggarwal in late January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/tempers-song-shoot-underway.html|title=Temper<U+2019>s song shoot underway|publisher=123telugu.com|date=26 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128165805/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/tempers-song-shoot-underway.html|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trailer-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46044911.cms|title=Trailer: NTR's Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128154135/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trailer-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46044911.cms?|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref> The entire filming came to an end on 31 January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/temper-shoot-wrapped-up.html|title=Temper shoot wrapped up|publisher=123telugu.com|date=31 January 2015|accessdate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150131130214/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/temper-shoot-wrapped-up.html|archivedate=31 January 2015}}</ref>

=== Post-production ===
S. R. Sekhar simultaneously completed the editing work so that the film can release on time.<ref name="editing"/> [[Post-production]] activities progressed in tandem with the filming during the film's shoot at Goa.<ref name="post prod"/> Mani Sharma began composing the background score on 4 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Mani-Sharma-Starts-Working-For-temper-telugu-news-120168|title=Mani Sharma starts working for 'Temper'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=4 December 2014|accessdate=4 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141204093940/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Mani-Sharma-Starts-Working-For-temper-telugu-news-120168|archivedate=4 December 2014}}</ref> The film's [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbing]] activities began on 9 December 2014 at Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/dubbing-kick-starts-for-ntrs-temper.html|title=Dubbing kick starts for NTR<U+2019>s Temper|publisher=123telugu.com|date=9 December 2014|accessdate=9 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141209074910/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/dubbing-kick-starts-for-ntrs-temper.html|archivedate=9 December 2014}}</ref> Rama Rao Jr. and the film's cast began dubbing for their roles on 4 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-starts-dubbing-for-temper.html|title=NTR starts dubbing for Temper|publisher=123telugu.com|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150204122143/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/ntr-starts-dubbing-for-temper.html|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-readying-for-release/articleshow/46122163.cms|title=NTR's Temper readying for release|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=5 February 2015|accessdate=5 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150205030432/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-readying-for-release/articleshow/46122163.cms?|archivedate=5 February 2015}}</ref> The pending DTS mixing and Rama Rao Jr.'s dubbing were completed by 7 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nithin-raves-about-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46163931.cms|title=Nithin raves about NTR's Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=9 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150209031237/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nithin-raves-about-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46163931.cms?|archivedate=9 February 2015}}</ref> Mani Sharma was completing the rerecording work at the same time and the final copy was planned to be sent to [[Central Board of Film Certification]] for censoring on 9 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Censor-Date-telugu-news-124931|title='Temper' censor date|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 February 2015|accessdate=7 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150207093546/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Censor-Date-telugu-news-124931|archivedate=7 February 2015}}</ref> The censoring activities were postponed by a day due to unavailability of slot for censor and delay of final mixing. The special screening for the board began at 4:00 PM.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-censor-process-underway-u-which-certificate-will-jr-ntr-starrer-get-623073|title='Temper' Censor Process Underway: A or U/A - Which Certificate will Jr NTR Starrer Get?|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=10 February 2015|accessdate=10 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150210132604/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-censor-process-underway-u-which-certificate-will-jr-ntr-starrer-get-623073|archivedate=10 February 2015}}</ref> The board passed the film with an 'U/A' certificate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Censor-Completed-telugu-news-125202|title='Temper' censor completed|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=10 February 2015|accessdate=10 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150210133042/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Censor-Completed-telugu-news-125202|archivedate=10 February 2015}}</ref> The film's final length after censoring was 147 minutes and 18 cuts were made in the film including the reduction of the climax by 30%.<ref name="run time"/>

== Themes and influences ==
In an interview with [[Subhash K. Jha]] for the newspaper ''Absolute India'', Puri Jagannadh said that the film is basically the story of a bad police officer played by Rama Rao Jr. and is an action-oriented film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.absoluteindianews.com/storydetail.php?nid=12538|title=Second time lucky?|author=[[Subhash K. Jha|K. Jha, Subhash]]|publisher=''Absolute India''|date=11 December 2014|accessdate=13 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141213141716/http://www.absoluteindianews.com/storydetail.php?nid=12538|archivedate=13 December 2014}}</ref> He added later that the film about a highly corrupt and cunning police officer who later transforms into an honest one and the title of the film signifies the protagonist's character has attitude, arrogance and is defiant. He added that the film has a novel theme and is not inspired by anyone in real life.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150204/entertainment-tollywood/article/there%E2%80%99s-no-affair-charmme-puri-jagannath|title=There<U+2019>s no affair with Charmme: Puri Jagannath|last=Varma|first=Lopsika|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=5 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150205031033/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150204/entertainment-tollywood/article/there%E2%80%99s-no-affair-charmme-puri-jagannath|archivedate=5 February 2015}}</ref> A source from the film's unit revealed that the confrontation scene in the courtroom was shot on the lines of a similar scene from the film ''[[Bobbili Puli]]'' (1982) and features N. T. Rama Rao Jr. delivering dialogues that ridicule the contemporary judicial system and police hierarchy.<ref name="court room"/>

== Music ==
{{Main|Temper (soundtrack)}}

[[Anoop Rubens]] was signed in on to compose the film's soundtrack album after Rama Rao Jr. insisted Jagannadh to bring a relatively new music composer on board when the latter opted for [[Devi Sri Prasad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Tempers-tempo-critical/articleshow/45932322.cms|title=Temper<U+2019>s tempo critical|last=Kamal|first=S. S.|publisher=''Bangalore Mirror''|date=18 January 2015|accessdate=26 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150126100211/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Tempers-tempo-critical/articleshow/45932322.cms?|archivedate=26 January 2015}}</ref> It consists of six songs all composed by Rubens and penned by Bhaskarabhatla, Kandikonda and Viswa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Original-Track-List-telugu-news-124085|title='Temper' Original Track List|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=27 January 2015|accessdate=27 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150127144852/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Original-Track-List-telugu-news-124085|archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref> Rahul Kumar, mostly known as Roll Rida, rapped for the songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/hyderabad/From-ragging-to-rapping/2015/01/29/article2641150.ece|title=From ragging to rapping|last=Yellapuntala|first=Suhas|publisher=''[[The New Indian Express]]''|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150130092153/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/hyderabad/From-ragging-to-rapping/2015/01/29/article2641150.ece|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref> The soundtrack was marketed by [[Aditya Music]] and was released on 28 January 2015 to positive reviews from critics.<ref name="Trailer OIE"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-audio-launch-watch-it-live-online-video-621746|title=Jr NTR's 'Temper' Audio Launch: Watch it Live Online [VIDEO]|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128144740/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-audio-launch-watch-it-live-online-video-621746|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref>

== Release ==
The film was initially planned for a worldwide theatrical release on 9 January 2015 as a [[Sankranthi]] release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntr-puri-jagannadh-film-to-have-a-sankranthi-release-telugu-news-107664|title=NTR - Puri Jagannadh film to have a Sankranthi release|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=19 May 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128141851/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntr-puri-jagannadh-film-to-have-a-sankranthi-release-telugu-news-107664|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/junior-ntr-film-with-puri-jagannadh-slated-for-makar-sankranti-114080200563_1.html|title=Junior NTR film with Puri Jagannadh slated for Makar Sankranti|author=IANS|publisher=[[Business Standard]]|date=2 August 2014|accessdate=22 August 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128141932/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/junior-ntr-film-with-puri-jagannadh-slated-for-makar-sankranti-114080200563_1.html|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/sankranti-bonanza/article6630340.ece|title=Sankranti bonanza|publisher=''The Hindu''|date=24 November 2014|accessdate=29 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141129023144/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/sankranti-bonanza/article6630340.ece|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref> The film's release was postponed from Sankranthi to a later date due to halt in the film's shoot post Nandamuri Janakiram's death and an official confirmation was awaited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-out-sankranti-race-617243|title=Junior NTR's 'Temper' Out of Sankranti Race?|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=15 December 2014|accessdate=15 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141215161925/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-out-sankranti-race-617243|archivedate=15 December 2014}}</ref> Later the film was expected to release in February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/pawan-kalyans-gopala-gopala-mahesh-babu-siva-film-top-10-most-awaited-telugu-films-2015-618497|title=From Pawan Kalyan's 'Gopala Gopala' to Mahesh Babu-Siva Film: Top 10 Most-Awaited Telugu Films of 2015|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=28 December 2014|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141228220459/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/pawan-kalyans-gopala-gopala-mahesh-babu-siva-film-top-10-most-awaited-telugu-films-2015-618497|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref> The release date was speculated as 13 February 2015 and an official confirmation was awaited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-release-date-postponed/articleshow/45980321.cms|title=NTR's Temper release date postponed|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=22 January 2015|accessdate=22 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150122160632/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-release-date-postponed/articleshow/45980321.cms|archivedate=22 January 2015}}</ref> Rama Rao Jr. was expected to announce the film's release date at the audio launch event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150124/entertainment-tollywood/article/big-day-jr-ntr|title=Big day for Jr NTR|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=24 January 2015|accessdate=25 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150125033209/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150124/entertainment-tollywood/article/big-day-jr-ntr|archivedate=25 January 2015}}</ref>

Bandla Ganesh announced at the audio launch that the film would release worldwide on 13 February 2015 at 05:07 AM.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Bandla-Ganesh-Confirms-temper-Release-Muhurat-telugu-news-124162|title=Bandla Ganesh confirms 'Temper' release Muhurat|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129042204/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Bandla-Ganesh-Confirms-temper-Release-Muhurat-telugu-news-124162|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> 90 theaters were booked in [[Karnataka]] for the film's release which is a big number for any Telugu film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Big-Release-For-temper-In-Karnataka-telugu-news-124973|title=Big release for 'Temper' in Karnataka|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 February 2015|accessdate=7 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150207094039/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Big-Release-For-temper-In-Karnataka-telugu-news-124973|archivedate=7 February 2015}}</ref> Great India Films was expected to release the film in 125 screens across the overseas markets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Temper-gets-good-buzz-in-overseas/articleshow/46173007.cms|title=Temper gets good buzz in overseas|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=10 February 2015|accessdate=10 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150210100035/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Temper-gets-good-buzz-in-overseas/articleshow/46173007.cms?|archivedate=10 February 2015}}</ref> The film was expected to release in 1500 theaters across the world. Advance booking of tickets began on 10 February and the tickets for the first day in AP/Nizam were sold out completely while Bangalore and Chennai witnessed an advance booking of 50% each within a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-set-grand-release-jr-ntr-kajal-starrer-registers-good-amount-advance-ticket-bookings-623134|title='Temper' Set for Grand Release; Jr NTR-Kajal Starrer Registers Good Amount of Advance Ticket Bookings|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''[[International Business Times|International Business Times India]]''|date=11 February 2015|accessdate=11 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150211152023/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-set-grand-release-jr-ntr-kajal-starrer-registers-good-amount-advance-ticket-bookings-623134|archivedate=11 February 2015}}</ref>

One of the benefit shows were held at Mallikarjuna 70 MM theater in KPHB colony at 4:00 AM. The other benefit show was held at Sreeramulu 70 MM theater in Moosapet at 5:00 AM. The ticket rates of these benefit shows ranged between {{INR}}2000 - {{INR}}5000 each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-benefit-shows-rajamouli-watch-jr-ntrs-film-tickets-selling-2000-5000-623227|title='Temper' Benefit Shows: Rajamouli to Watch Jr NTR's Film; Tickets Selling at <U+20B9>2000 to <U+20B9>5000?|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=12 February 2015|accessdate=12 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150212092259/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-benefit-shows-rajamouli-watch-jr-ntrs-film-tickets-selling-2000-5000-623227|archivedate=12 February 2015}}</ref> The film released in [[Japan]] on 28 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Released-In-Japan-telugu-news-126705|title='Temper' released in Japan|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=28 February 2015|accessdate=28 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150228143504/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Released-In-Japan-telugu-news-126705|archivedate=28 February 2015}}</ref>

=== Distribution ===
N. T. Rama Rao Jr. and Puri Jagannadh acquired the distribution rights of [[Telangana|Nizam region]] and [[Vishakhapatnam]]. Later Vakkantham Vamsi was reported to acquire the distribution rights of [[Nellore district]] for an amount of {{INRConvert|20|m}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Nellore-Rights-Bought-By-Vakkantham-Vamsi-telugu-news-120280|title='Temper' Nellore rights bought by Vakkantham Vamsi|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=6 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141206065135/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Nellore-Rights-Bought-By-Vakkantham-Vamsi-telugu-news-120280|archivedate=6 December 2014}}</ref> Great India Films announced in mid-January 2015 that they acquired the overseas distribution rights of the film. It was their third and fifth film with Puri Jagannadh and Rama Rao Jr. in overseas respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-In-Overseas-By-Great-India-Films-telugu-news-123319|title=NTR's 'TEMPER' in overseas by Great India Films|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=17 January 2015|accessdate=17 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150117072258/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-In-Overseas-By-Great-India-Films-telugu-news-123319|archivedate=17 January 2015}}</ref> DBB Films announced later that they acquired the distribution and theatrical screening rights of the film in [[Europe]] except [[United Kingdom]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-europe.html|title=NTR<U+2019>s "TEMPER" in EUROPE except UK by DBB Films|publisher=Idlebrain.com|date=22 January 2015|accessdate=22 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150122161043/http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-europe.html|archivedate=22 January 2015}}</ref> whose theatrical screening rights were acquired by Colours Media later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-uk.html|title=Temper movie UK rights|publisher=Idlebrain.com|date=24 January 2015|accessdate=26 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150126101341/http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-uk.html|archivedate=26 January 2015}}</ref> Sumanth Sunkara acquired the distribution rights of the film in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-canada.html|title=TEMPER in Canada|publisher=Idlebrain.com|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150130073231/http://www.idlebrain.com/abroad/temper-canada.html|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref>

The film's distribution rights for different regions have been sold for an amount of {{INR}}424 million out of which the highest amount was received from Nizam region rights which were bought by Suresh Movies with an advance of {{INR}}110 million followed by overseas rights for an amount of {{INR}}630 million and followed by [[Rayalaseema|Ceded region]] rights bought by Siva Shakti films for an amount of {{INR}}60 million.<ref name="Dist total">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-puris-temper-earns-over-50-crore-pre-release-business-622479|title=Junior NTR-Puri's 'Temper' Earns Over <U+20B9>50 crore in Pre-Release Business|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150204153721/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-puris-temper-earns-over-50-crore-pre-release-business-622479|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref> Anu Sri films and Suresh Movies acquired the [[East Godavari district|East]] and [[West Godavari district]]s' distribution rights for an amount of {{INR}}25.2 million and {{INR}}230 million respectively.<ref name="Dist total"/> The distribution rights of [[Guntur district|Guntur]] and Nellore districts were acquired by S Creations and Icon for an amount of {{INR}}330 million and {{INR}}12.5 million plus {{INR}}4 million advance respectively. Alankar Pictures offered {{INR}}30 million advance while Hari Pictures offered {{INR}}24.5 million for [[Krishna district]] rights on NRA basis.<ref name="Dist total"/> Brunda Associates acquired [[Karnataka]] distribution rights for {{INR}}45 million while SPI acquired [[Tamil Nadu]] distribution rights. [[North India]] distribution rights were sold for {{INR}}5 million.<ref name="Dist total"/>

=== Marketing ===
On 19 May 2014, 2 posters of this film bearing the title ''Production no. 5'' were released wishing N. T. Rama Rao Jr. a happy birthday in advance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntrs-birthday-special-poster-designs-telugu-news-107674|title=NTR's birthday special poster designs|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=19 May 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128140524/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ntrs-birthday-special-poster-designs-telugu-news-107674|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> The makers planned to reveal the film's first look teaser on [[Diwali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Puri-film-first-look-for-Diwali/articleshow/44740746.cms|title=NTR, Puri film first look for Diwali?|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=9 October 2014|accessdate=10 October 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128140633/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-Puri-film-first-look-for-Diwali/articleshow/44740746.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> The makers later decided to unveil the film's first look poster on November 29 and teaser on December 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Release-Date-And-Venue-Confirmed-telugu-news-119588|title='Temper' audio release date and venue confirmed|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128141039/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Release-Date-And-Venue-Confirmed-telugu-news-119588|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-Is-Bullet-Of-Jagun-:-Rgv-telugu-news-119622|title=NTR is bullet of Ja'gun' : RGV|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128140824/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-Is-Bullet-Of-Jagun-:-Rgv-telugu-news-119622|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Bandla Ganesh unveiled the official logo of the film's title on November 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-official-logo-unveiled-first-look-release-29-november-615321|title=Jr NTR's 'Temper' Official Logo Unveiled; First Look to Release on 29 November?|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128140933/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-official-logo-unveiled-first-look-release-29-november-615321|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Puri Jagannadh unveiled two posters featuring Rama Rao Jr. on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141127/entertainment-kollywood/article/first-look-jr-ntr-flaunts-chiseled-body-temper|title=First look: Jr NTR flaunts chiseled body in 'Temper'|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128141156/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141127/entertainment-kollywood/article/first-look-jr-ntr-flaunts-chiseled-body-temper|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-official-logo-unveiled-first-look-release-29-november-615321|title=Jr NTR Rocks in 'Temper' First-Look Posters; Official Logo Unveiled [PHOTOS]|author=Seshagiri, Sangeetha|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141128141232/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-official-logo-unveiled-first-look-release-29-november-615321|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> Another poster featuring Rama Rao Jr. was unveiled on 6 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-New-Poster-telugu-news-120303|title=NTR's 'Temper' New Poster|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=6 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141206064828/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-temper-New-Poster-telugu-news-120303|archivedate=6 December 2014}}</ref> In that poster, he was seen sporting a sky blue cotton shirt, white cargo pants and aviator sunglasses during the film's shoot at Goa. He posted the autographed version of the same in his official Facebook page a day before which received 30 thousand likes, 2 thousand shares and more than 1 thousand comments upon its release; all of them being positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-releases-new-poster-temper-fans-go-gaga-over-his-stylish-look-616382|title=Junior NTR Releases New Poster of 'Temper'; Fans Go Gaga over his Stylish Look|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=7 December 2014|accessdate=8 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141208055715/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntr-releases-new-poster-temper-fans-go-gaga-over-his-stylish-look-616382|archivedate=8 December 2014}}</ref>

The film's trailer was expected to be unveiled on or after 17 December 2014.<ref name="Temper resumes"/> A new still of Rama Rao Jr. was unveiled on 29 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-New-Still-From-temper-telugu-news-121963|title=NTR's new still from 'Temper'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=29 December 2014|accessdate=29 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141229092035/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntrs-New-Still-From-temper-telugu-news-121963|archivedate=29 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/New-Pic-Stylish-NTR-in-Temper/articleshow/45679105.cms|title=New Pic: Stylish NTR in Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=29 December 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141230012441/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/New-Pic-Stylish-NTR-in-Temper/articleshow/45679105.cms?|archivedate=30 December 2014}}</ref> The first look teaser was unveiled on 1 January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jr-ntrs-temper-balakrishnas-lion-teasers-be-unveiled-tonight-618904|title=New Year Treat: Jr NTR's 'Temper', Balakrishna's 'Lion' Teasers Released|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=31 December 2014|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6VFdriP25|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/watch-temper-movie-teaser-169201.html|title=WATCH: Temper Movie Teaser|author=Veena|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=1 January 2015|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6VFdZ5N5j|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trailer-New-teaser-of-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/45716056.cms|title=Trailer: New teaser of NTR's Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=1 January 2015|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150101163028/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trailer-New-teaser-of-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/45716056.cms?|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref> Two posters featuring Rama Rao Jr. were unveiled on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr--puri-Jagannadhs-temper-Latest-Posters-telugu-news-122203|title=NTR -Puri Jagannadh's 'Temper' latest posters|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=1 January 2015|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6VFfYCWIl|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref> The teaser was successful and the theatrical trailer of 1 minute duration was planned to be unveiled on the eve of [[Sankranthi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Theatrical-Trailer-Release-Date-telugu-news-122287|title='Temper' theatrical trailer release date|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=2 January 2015|accessdate=3 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150103064905/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Theatrical-Trailer-Release-Date-telugu-news-122287|archivedate=3 January 2015}}</ref> A poster featuring Rama Rao Jr. was unveiled on 24 January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-puris-temper-New-Poster-telugu-news-123912|title=NTR-Puri's 'Temper' new poster|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=24 January 2015|accessdate=24 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150124142810/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Ntr-puris-temper-New-Poster-telugu-news-123912|archivedate=24 January 2015}}</ref> Six audio release posters all featuring Rama Rao Jr. were unveiled on 27 January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Release-Posters-telugu-news-124043|title='Temper' audio release posters|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=27 January 2015|accessdate=27 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150127081216/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Audio-Release-Posters-telugu-news-124043|archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref> Another poster featuring Rama Rao Jr. and Kajal Aggarwal was unveiled on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Spotted-Kajal-and-NTR-romance-at-beach/articleshow/46030978.cms|title=Spotted: Kajal and NTR romance at beach|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=27 January 2015|accessdate=27 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150127132221/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Spotted-Kajal-and-NTR-romance-at-beach/articleshow/46030978.cms|archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref> A set of five stills featuring the lead pair and another five stills featuring Rama Rao Jr. were released on the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/temper1/index.html|title=Temper photo gallery - Telugu cinema - NTR & Kajal Agarwal|publisher=Idlebain.com|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128075327/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/temper1/index.html|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref>

[[File:Shilparamam.jpg|thumb|right|[[Shilpakala Vedika]], where the film's theatrical trailer was unveiled along with the soundtrack album and their video promos on 28 January 2015]]
The theatrical trailer with a duration of 116 seconds was unveiled on the night of 28 January 2015 at the audio launch. It received 0.25 million views, 3000 likes, 250 dislikes and more than 250 comments within 12 hours of it release in YouTube and received mixed feedback from audience.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-trailer-review-puri-jagannath-disappoints-junior-ntr-fans-621829|title='Temper' Trailer Review: Puri Jagannath Disappoints Junior NTR Fans [VIDEO]|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129071426/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-trailer-review-puri-jagannath-disappoints-junior-ntr-fans-621829|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> ''Deccan Chronicle'' opined that the trailer promised action and entertainment and would leave the audience asking for more.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150129/entertainment-tollywood/article/watch-jr-ntr-and-kajal-aggarwal-action-packed-temper-trailer|title=Watch Jr NTR and Kajal Aggarwal in the action-packed 'Temper' trailer|publisher=Deccan Chronicle|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129071958/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150129/entertainment-tollywood/article/watch-jr-ntr-and-kajal-aggarwal-action-packed-temper-trailer|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> Oneindia Entertainment wrote "As the trailer depicts him as a police officer, a dancer, a lover and a comedian and thus on a whole, ''Temper'' can be told as Jr. NTR in & as", adding that the trailer raised expectations.<ref name="Trailer OIE"/> IndiaGlitz stated "NTR looks very different and stylish compared to his previous films and he has even changed his body language and dialogue delivery. If the trailer is anything to go by, the film has plenty of action sequences and Puri mark witty dialogues. NTR fans are in for a treat."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Trailer-Review-telugu-news-124198|title='Temper' trailer review|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=29 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150129073542/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Trailer-Review-telugu-news-124198|archivedate=29 January 2015}}</ref> In contrast, Subramanian Harikumar of Bollywood Life stated "The obsession for cop roles amongst Telugu filmmakers is refusing to die down, as Jr NTR plays corrupt sub inspector Daya. Overall, ''Temper'' seems like it is the same run of the mill action entertainer, which would appeal to die hard Jr NTR fans and nothing more".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/temper-trailer-jr-ntr-shines-as-a-quirky-corrupt-cunning-cop/|title=Temper trailer: Jr NTR shines as a quirky, corrupt, cunning cop!|last=Harikumar|first=Subramanian|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=28 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150128170012/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/temper-trailer-jr-ntr-shines-as-a-quirky-corrupt-cunning-cop/|archivedate=28 January 2015}}</ref> Meanwhile, the video promo of the item number ''Ittage Rechchipodam'' crossed more than 90 thousand views on the official channel in YouTube within 24 hours of its release. The dance moves of Rama Rao Jr. and Nora Fatehi received praise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Teaser-NTR-and-Nora-Fatehi-shake-a-leg-in-Temper/articleshow/46056182.cms|title=Teaser: NTR and Nora Fatehi shake a leg in Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=29 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150130044340/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Teaser-NTR-and-Nora-Fatehi-shake-a-leg-in-Temper/articleshow/46056182.cms|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref>

The 40 second video promo of the song ''Temper'' received praise particularly for Rama Rao Jr.'s dance movements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Song-video-NTRs-stunning-dance-moves/articleshow/46067405.cms|title=Song video: NTR's stunning dance moves|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150131054929/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Song-video-NTRs-stunning-dance-moves/articleshow/46067405.cms|archivedate=31 January 2015}}</ref> The theatrical trailer crossed half a million views within 18 hours of its release in YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/temper-theatrical-trailer-creates-a-storm-news-telugu-pb4t7Kbijddec.html|title='Temper' theatrical trailer creates a storm|publisher=Sify|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150131054540/http://www.sify.com/movies/temper-theatrical-trailer-creates-a-storm-news-telugu-pb4t7Kbijddec.html|archivedate=31 January 2015}}</ref> It crossed a million views on 1 February 2015 in Puri Jagannadh's official channel on YouTube making it one of the record breaking Telugu film trailers in YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-trailer-goes-viral/articleshow/46087721.cms|title=NTR's Temper trailer goes viral|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=1 February 2015|accessdate=1 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150201154043/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTRs-Temper-trailer-goes-viral/articleshow/46087721.cms|archivedate=1 February 2015}}</ref> The video promo of the song ''One More Time'' received positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Song-One-More-Time-from-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46087923.cms|title=Song: One More Time from NTR's Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=3 February 2015|accessdate=3 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150203064757/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Song-One-More-Time-from-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46087923.cms?|archivedate=3 February 2015}}</ref> Six new stills featuring Rama Rao Jr. along with a set of working stills were released on 4 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/temper2/index.html|title=Temper photo gallery - Telugu cinema - NTR & Kajal Agarwal|publisher=Idlebrain.com|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150204160145/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/temper2/index.html|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/working-temper/index.html|title=Temper Working Stills photo gallery - Telugu cinema - NTR & Kajal Agarwal|publisher=Idlebrain.com|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150204160259/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/photogallery/working-temper/index.html|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref> 60 stills were released by the makers later; most of them featured Rama Rao Jr. in stylish looks and a few of them featuring the roles played by the remaining star cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-pictures-send-temperatures-soaring-photos-622956|title=Junior NTR's 'Temper' Pictures Send Temperatures Soaring [PHOTOS]|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=9 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150209165325/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-pictures-send-temperatures-soaring-photos-622956|archivedate=9 February 2015}}</ref>

=== Home media ===
The film satellite rights were sold for an amount of {{INR}}77.5 million to an undisclosed leading channel thus beating the record set by Rama Rao Jr.'s previous film ''[[Rabhasa]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-satellite-rights-sold-record-price-beats-rabhasa-619979|title=Junior NTR's 'Temper' Satellite Rights Sold at Record Price; Beats 'Rabhasa'|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=10 January 2015|accessdate=19 January 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150119164845/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/junior-ntrs-temper-satellite-rights-sold-record-price-beats-rabhasa-619979|archivedate=19 January 2015}}</ref> The television broadcast rights were sold to [[Gemini TV]] for an amount of {{INR}}78 million who faced a stiff competition from [[MAA TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Satellite-Rights-For-Gemini-Tv-telugu-news-125766|title='Temper' satellite rights for Gemini TV|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=17 February 2015|accessdate=17 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150217134951/http://www.indiaglitz.com/temper-Satellite-Rights-For-Gemini-Tv-telugu-news-125766|archivedate=17 February 2015}}</ref>

== Reception ==

=== Critical reception ===
The film received positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-review-round-jr-ntr-gets-thumbs-critics-623400|title='Temper' Review Round Up: Jr. NTR Gets Thumbs Up from Critics|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213120804/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-review-round-jr-ntr-gets-thumbs-critics-623400|archivedate=13 February 2015}}</ref> Y. Sunita Chowdary of ''[[The Hindu]]'' praised Rama Rao Jr.'s performance as one of his finest works and added "The strength of the story lies in Puri Jagan<U+2019>s clarity, at no moment he is in a hurry or tempted to show the hero<U+2019>s softer side. What this film needed desperately was personality and character and this time it gets both".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/temper-ntr-at-his-best/article6891552.ece|title=Temper: NTR at his best|last=Chowdary|first=Y. Sunita|publisher=''The Hindu''|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213155745/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/temper-ntr-at-his-best/article6891552.ece|archivedate=13 February 2015}}</ref> [[IBN Live]] called it the best work of Rama Rao Jr. after ''[[Rakhi (2006 film)|Rakhi]]'' (2006) and added "Although the film isn't targeted mainly at family audience due to overtly dealt perverted ideas, ''Temper'' can be a best watch for Nandamuri Fans".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/temper-review-after-rakhi-this-is-the-best-film-by-junior-ntr/528274-71-177.html|title='Temper' review: After Rakhi, this is the best film by Junior NTR|publisher=IBN Live|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213160549/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/temper-review-after-rakhi-this-is-the-best-film-by-junior-ntr/528274-71-177.html|archivedate=13 February 2015}}</ref> Hemanth Kumar of ''The Times of India'' gave the film 3.5 out of 5 stars and praised Rama Rao Jr.'s performance and the film's underlying theme. He wrote "In the end, ''Temper'' comes across as a film which was meant for NTR to reinvent himself, for Puri to prove that he hasn't lost his mojo yet, for NTR's fans, whose unflinching faith in the actor hasn't diminished at all".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/Temper/movie-review/46235000.cms|title=Temper Movie Review|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6WJYfAuEi|archivedate=13 February 2015}} {{rating|3.5|5}}</ref>

Pravallika Anjuri of [[Oneindia.in|Oneindia Entertainment]] gave the film 3.5 out of 5 stars and stated "It is surely a brave attempt by the team to opt a script like this. ''Temper'' deals with a sensitive story and yet conveyed it with all the commercial elements that are needed for a film to click."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/reviews/2015/jr-ntrs-temper-movie-review-plot-and-story-critics-173687.html|title=Temper Movie Review - NTR's One Man Show!|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213100635/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/reviews/2015/jr-ntrs-temper-movie-review-plot-and-story-critics-173687.html|archivedate=13 February 2015}} {{rating|3.5|5}}</ref> IndiaGlitz too gave 3.25 out of 5 stars and summarised "All in all, this one has emotion plus action, the former is the raison d' etre. Watch out for NTR. He is different and genuinely different here."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Temper-telugu-movie-review-19255|title=Temper Movie Review - NTR's durable act|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213055143/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Temper-telugu-movie-review-19255|archivedate=13 February 2015}} {{rating|3.25|5}}</ref> Suresh Kavirayani of ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'' gave the film 3 out of 5 stars. He praised the performances of Rama Rao Jr. and Prakash Raj and termed the film as one of the best films of the former's and also his ideal comeback.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150214/entertainment-movie-review/article/movie-review-temper-jr-ntr-back-bang|title=Movie review 'Temper': Jr NTR is back with a bang|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=''Deccan Chronicle''|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150214054920/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150214/entertainment-movie-review/article/movie-review-temper-jr-ntr-back-bang|archivedate=14 February 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> Subramanian Harikumar of Bollywood Life gave the film 3 out of 5 stars and stated "''Temper'' is one of those films which ride high on actor<U+2019>s performances and this film is a Jr NTR show from start to finish. Go in with minimum expectations and get ready to be mesmerised by NTR magic."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/temper-movie-review-jr-ntrs-charisma-saves-puri-jagannadhs-film/|title=Temper movie review: Jr NTR<U+2019>s charisma saves Puri Jagannadh<U+2019>s film!|last=Harikumar|first=Subramanian|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6WL1SDEbO|archivedate=14 February 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref>

In contrast, Haricharan Pudipeddi of [[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]] gave the film 3 out of 5 stars and termed ''Temper'' a regular Puri Jagannadh film salvaged by Rama Rao Jr.'s performance which he called a "terrific" one.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/temper-jr-ntr-saves-a-regular-puri-jagannadh-film-ians-telugu-movie-review-115021400380_1.html|title='Temper': Jr. NTR saves a regular Puri Jagannadh film (IANS Telugu Movie Review)|last=Pudipeddi|first=Haricharan|publisher=Business Standard|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150214092624/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/temper-jr-ntr-saves-a-regular-puri-jagannadh-film-ians-telugu-movie-review-115021400380_1.html|archivedate=14 February 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> [[Behindwoods]] gave the film 2.25 out of 5 stars and stated "A thin one-liner made into a film with underused artists and a disengaging screenplay! Thanks to the well-known faces, reasonable songs and Junior NTR's dance, ''Temper'' becomes bearable."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/temper/temper-review.html|title=Temper Movie Review|publisher=[[Behindwoods]]|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150213160857/http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/temper/temper-review.html|archivedate=13 February 2015}} {{rating|2.25|5}}</ref>

=== Box office ===
After including collections from Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Maharashtra, other parts of North India and international markets apart from AP/Nizam area, the first day total at the global box office stood approximately at {{INR}}150 million and became the biggest opener of Rama Rao Jr. after breaking the previous record set by ''[[Baadshah (2013 film)|Baadshah]]'' (2013).<ref name="Day 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-day-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-debuts-fantastic-response-623440|title='Temper' First Day Collection At Box Office: Jr NTR Starrer Beats 'Gopala Gopala' Record; Turns Biggest Opener of 2015|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150214090153/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-day-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-debuts-fantastic-response-623440|archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref> The film's trade witnessed around 50 per cent drop in the morning shows on its second day and improvements in the later shows and collected {{INR}}65 million taking its two day global box office total to approximately {{INR}}220 million.<ref name="Day 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-saturday-2nd-day-collection-box-office-ganesh-celebrates-its-success-jr-ntr-puri-623528|title='Temper' (Saturday) 2nd Day Collection At Box Office: Ganesh Celebrates its Success with Jr NTR, Puri [PHOTOS]|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=15 February 2015|accessdate=15 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150215051725/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-saturday-2nd-day-collection-box-office-ganesh-celebrates-its-success-jr-ntr-puri-623528|archivedate=15 February 2015}}</ref> Apart from AP/Nizam, the film collected {{INR}}35 million in other areas and the three day i.e. first weekend global box office total stood at {{INR}}281.8 million.<ref name="Day 3">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-weekend-3-days-box-office-collection-ntr-starrer-unaffected-by-sundays-india-vs-623585|title='Temper' First Weekend (3 Days) Box Office Collection: NTR Starrer Unaffected by Sunday's India vs Pakistan Match|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=16 February 2015|accessdate=16 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150216085433/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-weekend-3-days-box-office-collection-ntr-starrer-unaffected-by-sundays-india-vs-623585|archivedate=16 February 2015}}</ref>

The film's business witnessed a 70 percent drop on its fourth day and collected {{INR}}25 million and showed improvement on the next day which was [[Maha Shivaratri]] and collected {{INR}}32.5 million taking its five day global total to {{INR}}339.3 million.<ref name="Day 5">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-5-day-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-fares-well-maha-shivratri-holiday-623802|title='Temper' 5-Day Collection at Box Office: Jr NTR Starrer Fares Well on Maha Shivratri Holiday|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=18 February 2015|accessdate=18 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150218075720/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-5-day-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-fares-well-maha-shivratri-holiday-623802|archivedate=18 February 2015}}</ref> Trade Analyst Trinath told IANS that the film grossed {{INR}}400 million in six days and declared the film a [[Blockbuster (entertainment)|blockbuster]].<ref name="Day 6">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-6-days-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-mints-40-crore-worldwide-623958|title='Temper' (6 Days) Box Office Collection: Junior NTR Starrer Mints <U+20B9>40 Crore Worldwide|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=19 February 2015|accessdate=20 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150220052343/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-6-days-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-mints-40-crore-worldwide-623958|archivedate=20 February 2015}}</ref> By the end of its first week, the film collected {{INR}}380 million nett at the global box office and its distributors recovered 90 percent of their investments on the film by then. The film stood in the fifth place in the list of highest grossing Telugu film at the global box office in the first week and overtook ''Gopala Gopala'', ''[[Race Gurram]]'' (2014), ''Baadshah'' and ''[[Gabbar Singh (film)|Gabbar Singh]]'' (2012).<ref name="Day 7">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-7-days-first-week-collection-box-office-ntr-film-beats-gapala-gopala-record-624001|title='Temper' (7 Days) First Week Collection at Box Office: Jr NTR's Film Beats "Gapala Gopala", "Race Gurram", "Baadshah" Records|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=20 February 2015|accessdate=20 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150220115438/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-7-days-first-week-collection-box-office-ntr-film-beats-gapala-gopala-record-624001|archivedate=20 February 2015}}</ref>

''Temper'' lost many screens across the world due to new releases ''[[Bandipotu]]'' and ''Gayakudu'' and a couple of dubbed films because of which it witnessed a huge drop in its business. The film collected {{INR}}25 million on its eighth day at the global box office taking its eight day total to {{INR}}405 million.<ref name="Day 8">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-8-days-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-crosses-40-crore-mark-2nd-friday-624172|title='Temper' 8 Days Collection at Box Office: Jr NTR Starrer Crosses <U+20B9>40 crore Mark on 2nd Friday|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=21 February 2015|accessdate=21 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150221153904/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-8-days-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-crosses-40-crore-mark-2nd-friday-624172|archivedate=21 February 2015}}</ref> The film's business later witnessed a growth as the new releases received mixed reviews. It collected {{INR}}465 million nett by the end of its ten day run at the global box office with which the film overtook the second week collection of ''[[Govindudu Andarivadele]]'' (2014) and the lifetime collections of ''Gopala Gopala''.<ref name="Day 10">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-10-days-2nd-weekend-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-inching-towards-50-cr-mark-624260|title='Temper' (10 Days) 2nd Weekend Collection at Box Office: Jr NTR Starrer Inching towards <U+20B9>50 Cr Mark|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=23 February 2015|accessdate=23 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150223101142/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-10-days-2nd-weekend-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-inching-towards-50-cr-mark-624260|archivedate=23 February 2015}}</ref> The film witnessed a huge drop in its business due to new film releases and [[2015 Cricket World Cup]]. It collected {{INR}}495 million nett in 14 days at the global box office.<ref name="Day 14">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-2nd-week-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-fails-cross-50-crore-mark-14-days-624754|title='Temper' 2nd Week Collection at Box Office: Jr NTR Starrer Fails to Cross <U+20B9>50-crore Mark in 14 Days|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=27 February 2015|accessdate=27 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150227134240/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-2nd-week-collection-box-office-jr-ntr-starrer-fails-cross-50-crore-mark-14-days-624754|archivedate=27 February 2015}}</ref>

By the end of its 20 day run, the film crossed {{INR}}60 crore mark by grossing {{INR}}667.5 million and collected a distributor share of {{INR}}403.9 million.<ref name="Day 20">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-gross-66-75-crore-worldwide-625021|title='Temper' Box Office Collection: Junior NTR Starrer Gross <U+20B9>66.75 Crore Worldwide|last=Nicy|first=V. P.|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=2 March 2015|accessdate=3 March 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150303045340/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-gross-66-75-crore-worldwide-625021|archivedate=3 March 2015}}</ref> The film completed its 50 day run across several centres on 3 April 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/50-days-for-ntrs-temper-telugu-news-129437|title=50 days for NTR's 'Temper'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=3 April 2015|accessdate=3 April 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150403132246/http://www.indiaglitz.com/50-days-for-ntrs-temper-telugu-news-129437|archivedate=3 April 2015}}</ref> In its lifetime, the film grossed {{INR}}743 million and collected a share of {{INR}}431 million and was declared a profitable film for its distributors on a whole.<ref name="lifetime">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-50-days-collection-box-office-junior-ntr-starrer-fails-surpass-50-cr-mark-629203|title='Temper' 50 Days Collection at Box Office: Junior NTR Starrer Fails to Surpass <U+20B9>50 Cr Mark|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=14 April 2015|accessdate=14 April 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150414153352/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-50-days-collection-box-office-junior-ntr-starrer-fails-surpass-50-cr-mark-629203|archivedate=14 April 2015}}</ref> 

==== India ====
The film collected {{INR}}96.8 million at AP/Nizam box office and became the biggest opener for both Rama Rao Jr. in his career and Telugu cinema in 2015. It overtook the opening day collections of ''[[Gopala Gopala (2015 film)|Gopala Gopala]]'' at AP/Nizam box office thus emerging as the third highest opener of all time there.<ref name="Day 1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/temper-first-day-box-office-collection-173869.html|title=Temper First Day Box Office Collection|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=15 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150215055450/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/temper-first-day-box-office-collection-173869.html|archivedate=15 February 2015}}</ref> It collected {{INR}}11 million from 125 shows at Bangalore box office on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/bengaluru-box-office-roy-temper-anegan-off-good-opening-garden-city-623456|title=Bengaluru Box Office: 'Roy', 'Temper', 'Anegan' off to a Good Opening in Garden City|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150214090306/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/bengaluru-box-office-roy-temper-anegan-off-good-opening-garden-city-623456|archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref> It collected {{INR}}40 million at AP/Nizam box office on its second day<ref name="Day 2"/> and its two day AP/Nizam box office total stood at {{INR}}136.8 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-15/tempers-scorching-success-temper-2-ahead.html|title=Temper's scorching success !!! Temper 2 ahead|publisher=Behindwoods|date=15 February 2015|accessdate=15 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150215103400/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-15/tempers-scorching-success-temper-2-ahead.html|archivedate=15 February 2015}}</ref> It collected {{INR}}45 million at AP/Nizam box office on its third day taking its three day total to {{INR}}181.8 million breaking the opening weekend record of ''Gopala Gopala''.<ref name="Day 3"/> The film continued a steady run on its sixth day collecting {{INR}}17.8 million at AP/Nizam box office.<ref name="Day 6"/>

The film collected approximately {{INR}}240 million at AP/Nizam box office in its first week.<ref name="Day 7"/> The film collected {{INR}}97 million in ten days in Nizam region making ''Temper'' the biggest grosser of Rama Rao Jr. in that area beating the lifetime collections of his previous films ''[[Rabhasa]]'' (2014), ''[[Ramayya Vasthavayya]]'' (2013), ''[[Brindavanam (film)|Brindavanam]]'' (2010) and ''[[Dammu]]'' (2012), which collected {{INR}}69 million, {{INR}}89 million, {{INR}}83 million and {{INR}}82 million respectively in Nizam region in their lifetime. However it failed to break the records set by ''Race Gurram'' and ''Govindudu Andarivadele'' in Nizam region.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-jr-ntr-starrer-fails-beat-race-gurram-gav-records-nizam-624425|title='Temper' Box Office Collection: Jr NTR Starrer Fails to Beat 'Race Gurram', 'GAV' Records in Nizam|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=24 February 2015|accessdate=24 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150224153445/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-jr-ntr-starrer-fails-beat-race-gurram-gav-records-nizam-624425|archivedate=24 February 2015}}</ref> The film grossed {{INR}}393 million and collected {{INR}}272.5 million in ten days at AP/Nizam box office and topped the business charts in that area followed by ''[[Bandipotu]]'' and ''[[Badlapur (film)|Badlapur]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/weekend-box-office-collection-jr-ntrs-temper-leads-andhra-followed-by-bandipotu-badlapur-624444|title=Weekend Box Office Collection: Jr NTR's 'Temper' Leads in Andhra, Followed by 'Bandipotu', 'Badlapur'|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=24 February 2015|accessdate=25 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150225095933/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/weekend-box-office-collection-jr-ntrs-temper-leads-andhra-followed-by-bandipotu-badlapur-624444|archivedate=25 February 2015}}</ref>

The film grossed {{INR}}440 million and collected {{INR}}290.2 million at AP/Nizam box office by the end of its 20 day run. The film continued to stand in the first spot in the weekend business charts of AP/Nizam box office followed by ''[[Aambala|Maga Maharaju]]'', ''[[Pisaasu|Pisachi]]'', ''Ram Leela'' and ''Badlapur''.<ref name="Day 20"/> The film grossed {{INR}}58.5 million and collected {{INR}}24.5 million at Bangalore box office while the share and gross in the rest of Karnataka were reported as {{INR}}23 million and {{INR}}45 million respectively. The film grossed {{INR}}36 million and collected {{INR}}14 million in the rest of India including Tamil Nadu.<ref name="Day 20"/> The film grossed {{INR}}506 million and collected {{INR}}313.5 million at AP/Nizam box office in its lifetime. The lifetime gross and share figures at Karnataka, Tamil Nadu and the rest of India stood at {{INR}}115 million and {{INR}}51 million, {{INR}}14 million and {{INR}}5.5 million, {{INR}}22 million and {{INR}}8.5 million respectively.<ref name="lifetime"/>

==== Overseas ====
[[Taran Adarsh]] reported that the film collected US$256,834 on Thursday preview shows, US$228,779 on its first day, US$203,794 on its second day and US$163,395 on the third day at the United States box office taking its opening weekend total to US$852,802 in the country. It was equivalent to {{INR}}53 million and Adarsh called it a "flying start".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-weekend-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-kajal-aggarwal-starrer-earns-5-32-cr-623695|title='Temper' First Weekend Box Office Collection: Junior NTR-Kajal Aggarwal Starrer Earns <U+20B9> 5.32 Cr in US|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=17 February 2015|accessdate=17 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150217072013/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-first-weekend-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-kajal-aggarwal-starrer-earns-5-32-cr-623695|archivedate=17 February 2015}}</ref> It performed better than the other releases ''[[Roy (film)|Roy]]'' and ''[[Anegan]]'' which collected US$133,453 and US$105,070 equivalent to {{INR}}8.3 million and {{INR}}6.53 million respectively. The film was expected to cross the US$1 million mark soon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-us-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-beats-roy-anegan-may-cross-1-million-623755|title='Temper' US Box Office Collection: Junior NTR Starrer Beats 'Roy', 'Anegan'; May Cross $1 Million Mark|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=17 February 2015|accessdate=17 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150217104615/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-us-box-office-collection-junior-ntr-starrer-beats-roy-anegan-may-cross-1-million-623755|archivedate=17 February 2015}}</ref> The film collected US$934,467 in six days at the United States box office which was equivalent to {{INR}}58.2 million and was declared Rama Rao Jr.'s biggest success in the country.<ref name="Day 6"/>

The film collected US$23,000 each on 20 and 21 February 2015 at the United States box office and crossed the US$1 million mark by collecting US$10,05,000 in 10 days. With this, ''Temper'' became Rama Rao Jr.'s second film to cross the US$1 million mark after ''Baadshah'' and also the first Indian film in 2015 to cross that mark.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-ntr-starrer-cross-1-million-mark-us-624261|title='Temper' Box Office Collection: NTR Starrer Cross $1 Million Mark in US|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=23 February 2015|accessdate=23 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150223080022/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-box-office-collection-ntr-starrer-cross-1-million-mark-us-624261|archivedate=23 February 2015}}</ref> The lifetime gross and share figures at the United States stood at {{INR}}66 million and {{INR}}42.5 million respectively. The film grossed {{INR}}20 million and collected a shae of {{INR}}10 million in its lifetime in other international markets.<ref name="lifetime"/>

== Sequel and remake ==
Bandla Ganesh announced the film's sequel titled ''Temper 2'' on 14 February 2015 through his Twitter page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Bandla-Ganesh-Announces-temper-2-telugu-news-125587|title=Bandla Ganesh announces 'Temper 2'|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=15 February 2015|accessdate=15 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150215102950/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Bandla-Ganesh-Announces-temper-2-telugu-news-125587|archivedate=15 February 2015}}</ref> Its feasibility was doubted as Jagannadh shelved the sequels of his films ''[[Pokiri]]'' (2006) and ''[[Businessman (film)|Businessman]]'' (2012) in the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Will-Puri-Jagannadh-Direct-temper-2--telugu-news-125649|title=Will Puri Jagannadh direct 'Temper 2' ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=16 February 2015|accessdate=17 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150217051904/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Will-Puri-Jagannadh-Direct-temper-2--telugu-news-125649|archivedate=17 February 2015}}</ref> [[Sachiin J Joshi]] announced that he would bankroll the Tamil and Hindi remakes of the film under his banner Viiking Media & Entertainment Pvt Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sachin-Joshi-to-remake-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46272919.cms|title=Sachin Joshi to remake NTR's Temper|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=18 February 2015|accessdate=18 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150218020426/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sachin-Joshi-to-remake-NTRs-Temper/articleshow/46272919.cms|archivedate=18 February 2015}}</ref> He however denied the rumours that he would reprise Ram Rao Jr. in the film's remakes and clarified that he is in talks with a big Bollywood actor for the Hindi remake.<ref name="remake">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-be-remade-hindi-tamil-sachiin-joshi-buys-jr-ntr-starrers-remake-rights-624075|title='Temper' To be Remade in Hindi, Tamil: Sachiin Joshi Buys Jr NTR Starrer's Remake Rights|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=''International Business Times India''|date=20 February 2015|accessdate=20 February 2015|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20150220120556/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/temper-be-remade-hindi-tamil-sachiin-joshi-buys-jr-ntr-starrers-remake-rights-624075|archivedate=20 February 2015}}</ref> Ganesh reportedly sold those rights to Joshi as a part of the of compensation to money he owed to him when the latter financed the former's production ''[[Govindudu Andarivadele]]'' (2014).<ref name="remake"/>

